00:01:01,440 --> 00:01:04,280
Excuse me...

2
00:02:11,440 --> 00:02:12,960
Come here, honey.

3
00:02:13,360 --> 00:02:15,360
So how did it go?

4
00:02:15,440 --> 00:02:17,720
Very well. We went towards
the dam, and then...

5
00:02:17,760 --> 00:02:18,680
How did it go?

6
00:02:18,760 --> 00:02:21,480
Very well. We went towards the dam,
and then to the old town.

7
00:02:21,680 --> 00:02:23,360
You don't like
the old town, do you?

8
00:02:23,880 --> 00:02:25,960
So did you have fun
with your friends?

9
00:02:26,240 --> 00:02:27,840
Did you have fun
with your friends?

10
00:02:28,080 --> 00:02:29,480
And were you a good boy?

11
00:02:29,880 --> 00:02:31,520
You were a good boy.

12
00:02:31,680 --> 00:02:34,400
You were mommy's good boy.

13
00:03:04,840 --> 00:03:06,840
So... how did it go?

14
00:03:12,360 --> 00:03:13,960
Very well.
Impeccably.

15
00:03:14,000 --> 00:03:15,320
We went towards the dam...

16
00:03:15,360 --> 00:03:17,240
But did he feel good?

17
00:03:18,560 --> 00:03:19,280
Excuse me?

18
00:03:19,680 --> 00:03:21,800
Did he feel good?
Fulfilled?

19
00:03:22,520 --> 00:03:25,400
He's somewhat of a loner.
He's anxious.

20
00:03:26,000 --> 00:03:28,000
He doesn't like the
company of other animals.

21
00:03:29,160 --> 00:03:31,400
No...
It went impeccably.

22
00:03:32,360 --> 00:03:33,600
He was with other dogs.

23
00:03:34,640 --> 00:03:35,480
They ran.

24
00:03:35,720 --> 00:03:38,040
And...

25
00:03:39,640 --> 00:03:40,840
they talked to each other.

26
00:03:40,880 --> 00:03:41,800
That's good.

27
00:03:42,480 --> 00:03:44,120
Very good.
Wonderful.

28
00:03:45,200 --> 00:03:46,080
Thank you.

29
00:03:47,480 --> 00:03:48,320
Thank you, madam.

30
00:03:55,040 --> 00:04:00,080
PRICELESS

31
00:04:00,960 --> 00:04:01,880
Honey?

32
00:04:05,480 --> 00:04:06,360
Honey?

33
00:04:09,680 --> 00:04:10,600
Honey?

34
00:04:11,680 --> 00:04:13,240
Jacques, I can't believe it.

35
00:04:16,040 --> 00:04:16,800
Get up.

36
00:04:17,320 --> 00:04:18,840
Come on.

37
00:04:19,480 --> 00:04:20,600
Get on the bed.

38
00:04:24,240 --> 00:04:25,120
Do you feel well?

39
00:04:25,480 --> 00:04:26,680
Very well.

40
00:04:28,280 --> 00:04:29,160
And you?

41
00:04:30,160 --> 00:04:31,480
You're completely drunk.

42
00:04:33,080 --> 00:04:35,160
It took you 3 hours to get ready.

43
00:04:35,400 --> 00:04:36,600
Look how much you've drunk.

44
00:04:36,640 --> 00:04:37,640
Don't worry.

45
00:04:38,120 --> 00:04:40,200
These are little bottles.

46
00:04:40,240 --> 00:04:41,880
You could have made an effort today.

47
00:04:41,920 --> 00:04:44,160
Don't argue with me, honey.

48
00:04:45,200 --> 00:04:48,120
I hate it when people
tell me the truth.

49
00:04:48,360 --> 00:04:49,440
Right.

50
00:04:50,480 --> 00:04:51,240
Don't move.

51
00:04:51,320 --> 00:04:52,560
I'll give you a second pillow.

52
00:04:54,120 --> 00:04:55,160
Thank you.

53
00:04:59,440 --> 00:05:02,680
In 2 minutes I'll
be at your disposal.

54
00:05:06,400 --> 00:05:07,600
Dammit.

55
00:05:19,480 --> 00:05:20,280
Jean?

56
00:05:21,160 --> 00:05:22,000
I'm sorry.

57
00:05:25,960 --> 00:05:27,040
You look awful.

58
00:05:28,040 --> 00:05:29,800
- Did you walk the dogs again?
- Yes.

59
00:05:29,880 --> 00:05:31,400
And today morning
I took care of supplies.

60
00:05:31,480 --> 00:05:33,080
Why do you accept this work?

61
00:05:33,800 --> 00:05:36,320
They're so used to me accepting,
that I don't dare refuse.

62
00:05:37,040 --> 00:05:38,080
Besides, I have the time.

63
00:05:38,320 --> 00:05:39,720
Do as you like.
It's not my problem.

64
00:05:40,520 --> 00:05:41,680
But don't fall asleep in the bar.

65
00:05:41,720 --> 00:05:42,720
Sure.
Of course.

66
00:05:43,200 --> 00:05:44,720
I'm sorry.
It won't happen again.

67
00:05:46,160 --> 00:05:46,960
I'm leaving now.

68
00:05:48,160 --> 00:05:49,680
- Can you close up?
- Yes, of course.

69
00:05:52,880 --> 00:05:55,000
He'll leave if
you turn down the lights.

70
00:06:00,000 --> 00:06:01,000
Excuse me.

71
00:06:01,200 --> 00:06:02,200
I'd like another one.

72
00:06:06,840 --> 00:06:08,440
It's good you turned
down the lights.

73
00:06:08,480 --> 00:06:09,520
It's nicer this way.

74
00:06:09,600 --> 00:06:10,640
Thank you, sir.

75
00:06:10,840 --> 00:06:14,120
Can you turn on the TV?
There's a live broadcast on Eurosport.

76
00:06:14,200 --> 00:06:15,040
Yes, sir.

77
00:06:19,720 --> 00:06:20,600
Sit down.

78
00:06:21,000 --> 00:06:22,520
I'm not allowed to
leave the bar, sir.

79
00:06:22,480 --> 00:06:23,360
Really?

80
00:06:23,360 --> 00:06:25,560
Really. Except to serve drinks and...

81
00:06:26,440 --> 00:06:27,520
in case of a fire.

82
00:06:28,680 --> 00:06:29,520
Yes, sir.

83
00:06:29,800 --> 00:06:30,760
Sit down.

84
00:06:45,120 --> 00:06:46,240
Have a cigar.

85
00:06:47,960 --> 00:06:49,400
Have a cigar.

86
00:06:55,680 --> 00:06:57,880
The leaves grow in
the middle of cocoa fields.

87
00:07:00,200 --> 00:07:02,880
That's what gives them
their particular aroma.

88
00:07:04,080 --> 00:07:05,000
Do you smell it?

89
00:07:05,520 --> 00:07:06,280
Yes, sir.

90
00:07:07,760 --> 00:07:10,440
Because of the embargo against Cuba,
I fly them in by private jet.

91
00:07:11,480 --> 00:07:13,600
One cigar costs about...

92
00:07:14,640 --> 00:07:15,760
120 euros.

93
00:08:27,480 --> 00:08:28,360
Good evening.

94
00:08:38,600 --> 00:08:39,360
I'm sorry.

95
00:08:39,600 --> 00:08:41,520
This is the first time
I've fallen asleep like this.

96
00:08:42,120 --> 00:08:44,400
Considering the mood here,
I don't see anything better to do.

97
00:08:45,400 --> 00:08:46,480
This place is dead.

98
00:08:46,520 --> 00:08:48,800
No. It was brimming with life earlier.

99
00:08:50,400 --> 00:08:51,480
But now it's a bit late.

100
00:08:51,640 --> 00:08:54,080
It's not normal, that there isn't
anyone at the bar at this hour.

101
00:08:55,160 --> 00:08:57,200
Normally, they aren't
allowed to leave before 3 a.m.

102
00:08:59,480 --> 00:09:00,560
It's forbidden.

103
00:09:01,080 --> 00:09:02,200
Unless there isn't anyone.

104
00:09:02,280 --> 00:09:03,240
But you're here.

105
00:09:04,000 --> 00:09:04,800
Yes.

106
00:09:05,720 --> 00:09:06,840
And I'm here, right?

107
00:09:07,600 --> 00:09:08,240
Indeed.

108
00:09:08,440 --> 00:09:10,240
Something like this wouldn't
happen at the Carlton.

109
00:09:10,520 --> 00:09:11,560
You know, the Carlton...

110
00:09:11,960 --> 00:09:13,840
Do you think their
service has worsened as well?

111
00:09:17,200 --> 00:09:18,400
Do you think he'll come back?

112
00:09:19,160 --> 00:09:19,760
Who?

113
00:09:19,880 --> 00:09:20,720
The barman.

114
00:09:23,560 --> 00:09:24,240
I don't know.

115
00:09:29,520 --> 00:09:31,040
Will you wait with me for him?

116
00:09:31,080 --> 00:09:32,560
Yes.
Of course, miss.

117
00:09:34,240 --> 00:09:35,000
That's nice of you.

118
00:09:38,280 --> 00:09:39,600
Your cigar smells nice.

119
00:09:40,320 --> 00:09:42,400
Normally I can't stand the smell,
but in this case...

120
00:09:43,640 --> 00:09:44,400
Yes...

121
00:09:46,360 --> 00:09:47,360
It's because of the leaves,

122
00:09:47,760 --> 00:09:50,840
which grow in the
middle of cocoa fields.

123
00:09:51,720 --> 00:09:52,440
Really?

124
00:09:54,360 --> 00:09:57,040
They're flown in from Cuba
by private jet because of the...

125
00:10:02,920 --> 00:10:03,760
Because of the embargo?

126
00:10:03,800 --> 00:10:04,480
That's it.

127
00:10:17,040 --> 00:10:17,880
Are you alright?

128
00:10:18,800 --> 00:10:20,120
Today is my birthday.

129
00:10:20,960 --> 00:10:22,280
Happy birthday, miss.

130
00:10:22,960 --> 00:10:24,200
It's off to a bad start.

131
00:10:30,560 --> 00:10:32,520
I wanted so much
to have fun tonight.

132
00:10:35,200 --> 00:10:37,760
I'd give anything for
a cocktail and some music.

133
00:10:50,480 --> 00:10:51,440
What are you doing?

134
00:10:52,200 --> 00:10:53,480
Cocktails are my specialty.

135
00:10:54,240 --> 00:10:55,200
Isn't this too risky?

136
00:10:55,680 --> 00:10:58,280
In the worst case,
I'll just say I work here.

137
00:11:08,840 --> 00:11:10,000
So what would you like?

138
00:11:10,400 --> 00:11:11,200
I don't know.

139
00:11:12,120 --> 00:11:13,480
Something that gives a feeling of joy.

140
00:11:13,520 --> 00:11:15,560
For your birthday I suggest
something with champagne.

141
00:11:15,600 --> 00:11:16,680
And that gets you drunk fast.

142
00:11:17,040 --> 00:11:18,200
Gets you drunk fast...
Then...

143
00:11:18,240 --> 00:11:19,160
A cocktail with champagne.

144
00:11:19,200 --> 00:11:20,240
Excellent.
Wonderful.

145
00:11:46,520 --> 00:11:48,240
I love to watch someone work.

146
00:11:49,200 --> 00:11:51,680
I'm always impressed by
people who can do something.

147
00:11:52,680 --> 00:11:53,720
I can't do anything.

148
00:11:54,800 --> 00:11:55,480
Actually I can.

149
00:11:55,960 --> 00:11:57,200
I can make conversation.

150
00:12:06,080 --> 00:12:06,680
And you?

151
00:12:08,000 --> 00:12:08,680
Right.

152
00:12:29,000 --> 00:12:29,880
I'll have another one.

153
00:13:06,320 --> 00:13:07,480
Which floor are you staying at?

154
00:13:07,880 --> 00:13:08,400
Me?

155
00:13:10,120 --> 00:13:10,760
Yes, you.

156
00:13:10,800 --> 00:13:11,480
The fifth...

157
00:13:12,400 --> 00:13:13,280
The fifth floor.

158
00:13:20,800 --> 00:13:21,920
The imperial suite.

159
00:13:24,600 --> 00:13:25,760
I only know the royal one.

160
00:13:29,760 --> 00:13:31,000
- Will you give me a tour?
- Sure.

161
00:13:33,800 --> 00:13:35,720
The dressing room.

162
00:13:41,880 --> 00:13:43,880
Here we have the living room.

163
00:13:47,880 --> 00:13:48,720
The living room.

164
00:13:49,120 --> 00:13:50,720
The first bathroom.

165
00:13:53,920 --> 00:13:57,360
Here we have the study, with
a wireless internet connection.

166
00:13:58,720 --> 00:13:59,720
And a fax.

167
00:14:02,200 --> 00:14:03,400
The bedroom.

168
00:14:04,640 --> 00:14:05,760
This way, please.

169
00:14:09,680 --> 00:14:11,320
You must be very rich.

170
00:14:11,920 --> 00:14:13,000
Why do you say that?

171
00:14:13,360 --> 00:14:15,120
Must I do everything for you?

172
00:14:15,320 --> 00:14:16,280
What?

173
00:14:31,360 --> 00:14:34,840
Happy... birthday... to... you...

174
00:14:35,920 --> 00:14:40,160
Happy... birthday... to... you...

175
00:15:22,800 --> 00:15:23,960
Did they leave the royal suite?

176
00:15:24,040 --> 00:15:24,920
They left this morning.

177
00:15:24,960 --> 00:15:26,120
They stole a bathrobe.

178
00:16:02,640 --> 00:16:08,680
ONE YEAR LATER...

179
00:16:20,640 --> 00:16:21,960
The coffee, ladies and gentlemen.

180
00:16:22,000 --> 00:16:23,280
Who'll be having the decaf?

181
00:16:53,880 --> 00:16:54,920
Excuse me.

182
00:16:56,600 --> 00:16:57,480
Excuse me.

183
00:16:59,560 --> 00:17:00,400
Is everything alright?

184
00:17:10,320 --> 00:17:11,280
Jean, but...

185
00:17:12,680 --> 00:17:13,440
What are you doing?

186
00:17:16,480 --> 00:17:17,520
Jean, are you alright?

187
00:17:21,360 --> 00:17:22,640
Thank you very much, sir.

188
00:17:26,520 --> 00:17:28,600
I'm not hungry.

189
00:17:28,640 --> 00:17:29,920
What will you have?

190
00:17:30,720 --> 00:17:32,120
What you picked.
Good idea.

191
00:17:32,560 --> 00:17:33,520
With pleasure.

192
00:17:38,680 --> 00:17:40,600
- Irene?
- Yes?

193
00:17:44,520 --> 00:17:45,760
Happy birthday.

194
00:17:56,800 --> 00:17:58,120
Thank you, Jacques.

195
00:18:39,600 --> 00:18:40,600
Are you alone?

196
00:18:43,200 --> 00:18:44,280
For the moment.

197
00:18:47,840 --> 00:18:48,960
And your...

198
00:18:49,720 --> 00:18:50,720
uncle?

199
00:18:51,600 --> 00:18:53,320
You're talking about my great-uncle?

200
00:18:54,520 --> 00:18:55,600
He's growing old.

201
00:18:57,080 --> 00:18:58,160
Will you have a cocktail?

202
00:19:00,080 --> 00:19:01,040
Just one?

203
00:19:50,320 --> 00:19:51,200
What the...

204
00:19:54,600 --> 00:19:56,640
Older people get up early.

205
00:19:57,280 --> 00:19:59,080
You should know that by now.

206
00:20:00,000 --> 00:20:01,800
I couldn't sleep at all.

207
00:20:02,680 --> 00:20:04,520
I went to the beach
to get some fresh air.

208
00:20:04,560 --> 00:20:06,520
I also couldn't sleep.

209
00:20:07,160 --> 00:20:09,960
And I saw you at the bar
with that guy.

210
00:20:10,000 --> 00:20:12,480
You were tenderly getting
some fresh air on the sofa.

211
00:20:16,560 --> 00:20:17,840
I'm sorry, Jacques.

212
00:20:18,520 --> 00:20:19,800
I don't know what came over me.

213
00:20:21,640 --> 00:20:23,360
That was the first time.
I swear.

214
00:20:47,960 --> 00:20:50,000
In a few months I'll see
you at the same place

215
00:20:50,040 --> 00:20:51,120
where I picked you up.

216
00:20:51,440 --> 00:20:53,440
At the hotel bar,
wearing a mini,

217
00:20:54,080 --> 00:20:55,800
with the same fake
expression of indifference.

218
00:20:56,360 --> 00:20:57,480
I'm not worried.

219
00:20:58,440 --> 00:21:01,000
You'll be so drunk
you'll ask me my name.

220
00:21:01,720 --> 00:21:03,360
You'll offer me a drink.

221
00:21:06,920 --> 00:21:08,240
Dammit.
I can't believe it.

222
00:21:09,240 --> 00:21:10,360
I'm so stupid.

223
00:21:25,520 --> 00:21:26,320
Dammit.

224
00:21:48,280 --> 00:21:49,160
Dammit.

225
00:21:53,040 --> 00:21:55,240
I left him.
I left it all for you.

226
00:22:03,520 --> 00:22:04,640
Did you forget something?

227
00:22:04,920 --> 00:22:05,880
I forgot you.

228
00:22:09,080 --> 00:22:09,920
Excuse me?

229
00:22:11,480 --> 00:22:13,600
But... weren't you supposed
to leave today?

230
00:22:15,120 --> 00:22:15,920
Jean?

231
00:22:17,320 --> 00:22:18,080
Yes?

232
00:22:20,560 --> 00:22:21,440
I left him.

233
00:22:23,560 --> 00:22:24,840
I left it all for you.

234
00:22:25,760 --> 00:22:26,600
Really?

235
00:22:26,760 --> 00:22:27,640
Yes.

236
00:22:29,720 --> 00:22:31,040
Tell me I did the right thing.

237
00:22:31,720 --> 00:22:32,800
You did the right thing.

238
00:22:46,160 --> 00:22:47,720
I want to spend every
hour with you.

239
00:22:54,760 --> 00:22:56,600
- Do you know what would make me happy?
- I don't.

240
00:22:57,000 --> 00:22:57,920
A trip to the Maldives.

241
00:22:58,360 --> 00:22:58,920
Where?

242
00:22:58,960 --> 00:23:00,400
The Maldive Islands.
You don't know them?

243
00:23:00,440 --> 00:23:03,360
I do.
But not all of them.

244
00:23:03,440 --> 00:23:06,040
But first we'll order
a big breakfast.

245
00:23:06,200 --> 00:23:07,880
When I'm happy
I'm also very hungry.

246
00:23:08,320 --> 00:23:10,400
And this time we'll
spend the morning in bed.

247
00:23:11,160 --> 00:23:13,040
You're not the type of person
who works all the time?

248
00:23:14,040 --> 00:23:14,880
That depends.

249
00:23:50,800 --> 00:23:51,920
Do something.

250
00:24:02,120 --> 00:24:04,640
Damn, what are you doing here?
Everyone downstairs is looking for you.

251
00:24:10,080 --> 00:24:11,960
Dammit.
I can't believe it.

252
00:24:23,480 --> 00:24:24,560
Get out of here.

253
00:24:24,600 --> 00:24:26,520
In 2 minutes I'm sending
Martine to clean the room.

254
00:24:26,560 --> 00:24:27,680
Damn, I can't believe it.

255
00:24:37,760 --> 00:24:39,080
I can't believe it's you.

256
00:25:07,440 --> 00:25:10,000
You've arrived in Nice.

257
00:25:10,040 --> 00:25:11,520
This is the last stop.

258
00:25:11,560 --> 00:25:13,760
We ask all passengers to
get off the train.

259
00:25:13,960 --> 00:25:16,680
We ask that you make sure you
haven't left anything on the train.

260
00:25:16,520 --> 00:25:18,600
The next train will
arrive at 2 o'clock.

261
00:25:29,400 --> 00:25:30,080
Henri?

262
00:25:30,320 --> 00:25:31,160
It's Irene.

263
00:25:31,720 --> 00:25:32,600
Irene Mercier.

264
00:25:33,040 --> 00:25:35,040
We met at that social gathering.

265
00:25:36,720 --> 00:25:38,320
At the casino in Cannes.

266
00:25:38,520 --> 00:25:39,440
Last year.

267
00:25:41,520 --> 00:25:42,400
I'm sorry.

268
00:25:42,720 --> 00:25:43,960
Yes, of course.

269
00:25:45,120 --> 00:25:46,240
Maybe some other time?

270
00:25:46,280 --> 00:25:48,840
My number is...
Bye.

271
00:25:49,440 --> 00:25:50,280
Asshole.

272
00:25:50,680 --> 00:25:51,440
Dominique?

273
00:25:51,800 --> 00:25:52,440
It's Irene.

274
00:25:54,400 --> 00:25:56,080
We met at the VIP club last year.

275
00:25:56,720 --> 00:25:58,720
You spilled your
glass on my dress.

276
00:25:59,640 --> 00:26:01,160
Irene.
That's right.

277
00:26:01,320 --> 00:26:02,200
Very well.

278
00:26:03,840 --> 00:26:04,680
For how long?

279
00:26:06,000 --> 00:26:06,760
Too bad.

280
00:26:07,760 --> 00:26:08,720
Baire?

281
00:26:08,840 --> 00:26:09,720
It's Irene.

282
00:26:09,760 --> 00:26:10,440
Ivan?

283
00:26:10,520 --> 00:26:11,360
It's Irene.

284
00:26:11,680 --> 00:26:14,040
Single, small but well-proportioned.

285
00:26:14,560 --> 00:26:15,800
Yes, Irene, that's right.

286
00:26:15,840 --> 00:26:16,960
Benoit?

287
00:26:17,200 --> 00:26:17,640
Asshole.

288
00:26:17,680 --> 00:26:18,520
Philippe?

289
00:26:18,560 --> 00:26:19,440
It's Irene.

290
00:26:21,160 --> 00:26:25,320
Don't you remember the meeting
in Dauville last year?

291
00:26:30,720 --> 00:26:31,560
I'm sorry.

292
00:26:33,080 --> 00:26:34,280
My condolences.

293
00:26:36,440 --> 00:26:37,840
Are you his son?

294
00:26:39,560 --> 00:26:40,640
Grandson?

295
00:26:41,760 --> 00:26:43,160
So we must be the same age.

296
00:27:11,760 --> 00:27:12,840
What are you doing here?

297
00:27:13,280 --> 00:27:16,280
Reception told me you asked for
the schedule of trains to Nice.

298
00:27:17,000 --> 00:27:18,480
I'm going around from
one bar to the next.

299
00:27:20,080 --> 00:27:21,000
I wanted to say I'm sorry.

300
00:27:23,360 --> 00:27:24,680
Fine, alright.

301
00:27:28,880 --> 00:27:29,600
Good bye.

302
00:27:29,840 --> 00:27:31,280
I didn't get the chance this morning.

303
00:27:33,400 --> 00:27:34,560
So I came by train.

304
00:27:35,360 --> 00:27:36,760
No kidding?
You didn't fly in by jet?

305
00:27:39,360 --> 00:27:40,720
I really wanted to say I'm sorry.

306
00:27:42,320 --> 00:27:43,600
I wanted to say it to you.

307
00:27:45,040 --> 00:27:47,040
I'm sorry for what I did.

308
00:27:47,760 --> 00:27:49,280
Fine.
You've said it now.

309
00:27:49,760 --> 00:27:50,480
So good bye.

310
00:27:50,480 --> 00:27:52,640
I thought we could go
have dinner together.

311
00:27:52,720 --> 00:27:54,280
Are you nuts?
I won't eat dinner with you.

312
00:27:54,520 --> 00:27:55,440
I want you to go away.

313
00:27:56,160 --> 00:27:57,000
I feel bad...

314
00:27:57,040 --> 00:27:58,360
I don't care how you feel.

315
00:27:58,680 --> 00:28:00,600
Do you understand? I don't care.
I have a date.

316
00:28:00,640 --> 00:28:01,480
So good bye.

317
00:28:02,320 --> 00:28:03,080
How about tomorrow?

318
00:28:05,680 --> 00:28:07,360
Do you know who that
was back at the hotel?

319
00:28:07,600 --> 00:28:09,160
We were going to get
married in 3 months.

320
00:28:09,480 --> 00:28:10,240
3 months.

321
00:28:10,320 --> 00:28:12,240
He adored me.
I even had an engagement ring.

322
00:28:12,440 --> 00:28:14,560
I'd be done with the bars,
the mini and the smiles.

323
00:28:14,640 --> 00:28:15,360
Do you understand?

324
00:28:15,400 --> 00:28:17,040
I'd be set until the end of my life.

325
00:28:17,080 --> 00:28:17,720
I'm sorry.

326
00:28:18,160 --> 00:28:20,000
So am I.
You don't know how badly.

327
00:28:20,520 --> 00:28:22,200
And now I have to start all over.

328
00:28:22,440 --> 00:28:23,920
So if you want to do me a favor,

329
00:28:25,160 --> 00:28:26,800
then just leave me alone.

330
00:28:31,520 --> 00:28:33,080
You don't have the
time for a drink?

331
00:28:34,200 --> 00:28:34,960
Dammit.

332
00:28:36,800 --> 00:28:38,600
It's probably the second to your left.

333
00:28:38,960 --> 00:28:41,200
You go out and it's
the second to your left.

334
00:28:41,680 --> 00:28:43,240
Going out, the second to your left.

335
00:28:44,000 --> 00:28:44,800
Going out.

336
00:28:45,480 --> 00:28:46,240
François?

337
00:28:47,200 --> 00:28:47,760
Yes.

338
00:28:49,200 --> 00:28:50,440
- Irene?
- Yes.

339
00:28:50,680 --> 00:28:52,200
- Good evening.
- Good evening.

340
00:28:54,960 --> 00:28:56,320
- Thank you.
- Thank you.

341
00:28:57,560 --> 00:29:00,440
I love Italian food,
because it's never pretentious.

342
00:29:00,960 --> 00:29:02,960
And we never expect
anything out of the ordinary,

343
00:29:03,000 --> 00:29:04,160
so we're never disappointed.

344
00:29:04,200 --> 00:29:04,720
Right?

345
00:29:06,040 --> 00:29:06,720
Indeed.

346
00:29:09,480 --> 00:29:10,400
It depends.

347
00:29:10,880 --> 00:29:14,160
But when in Italy, I don't like
to eat in the local restaurants.

348
00:29:15,080 --> 00:29:16,000
It's less amusing.

349
00:29:16,400 --> 00:29:18,600
Maybe because they don't make
the effort to act like Italians.

350
00:29:19,400 --> 00:29:20,120
Maybe.

351
00:29:22,720 --> 00:29:23,480
Listen...

352
00:29:24,360 --> 00:29:27,320
That guy next to the
cars is watching us.

353
00:29:28,360 --> 00:29:29,880
And I feel funny.

354
00:29:36,920 --> 00:29:37,840
But I don't know him.

355
00:29:38,160 --> 00:29:39,880
He was with you at
the bar when I arrived.

356
00:29:40,280 --> 00:29:42,440
And now he's here and
I think he's waiting for us.

357
00:29:43,840 --> 00:29:44,760
And I feel uneasy.

358
00:29:45,320 --> 00:29:45,880
I'm sorry.

359
00:29:46,520 --> 00:29:47,560
This is ridiculous, François.

360
00:29:47,720 --> 00:29:50,400
You seem to love pasta,
so you can eat mine.

361
00:29:56,280 --> 00:29:57,720
Can I leave you my number?

362
00:30:08,440 --> 00:30:10,200
Is your invitation to
dinner still open?

363
00:30:11,200 --> 00:30:11,960
Yes, of course.

364
00:30:12,400 --> 00:30:14,200
I found a really nice pizza
shop in the old town.

365
00:30:14,240 --> 00:30:16,600
No. I don't eat at nice pizza shops.

366
00:30:16,800 --> 00:30:17,960
Alright.
As you wish.

367
00:30:18,760 --> 00:30:20,720
120 EUROS
115 EUROS

368
00:30:22,800 --> 00:30:24,240
230 EUROS
180 EUROS

369
00:30:34,240 --> 00:30:35,840
I'd like some caviar.

370
00:30:39,840 --> 00:30:40,880
The crawfish.

371
00:30:42,200 --> 00:30:43,040
And some champagne.

372
00:30:44,240 --> 00:30:45,080
And you?

373
00:30:46,240 --> 00:30:47,120
What will you have?

374
00:30:49,920 --> 00:30:51,280
I don't know.
I need to think it over.

375
00:30:51,760 --> 00:30:53,160
Available at next delivery.

376
00:30:53,200 --> 00:30:53,760
What?

377
00:30:53,800 --> 00:30:55,920
The crawfish. It will be
available at next delivery.

378
00:30:56,560 --> 00:30:57,720
The delivery has just arrived.

379
00:30:59,480 --> 00:31:00,280
Good.

380
00:31:00,320 --> 00:31:01,080
I feel relieved.

381
00:31:03,480 --> 00:31:04,240
So?

382
00:31:05,480 --> 00:31:07,040
I need to leave you for a moment.

383
00:31:18,800 --> 00:31:20,000
Good evening, Mr. Molluquet.

384
00:31:20,040 --> 00:31:22,240
This is a message from Mr. Simon.

385
00:31:24,720 --> 00:31:29,200
Can you wire my bonus
to my current account?

386
00:31:30,040 --> 00:31:31,840
My whole bonus.

387
00:31:32,680 --> 00:31:34,760
Tomorrow morning.
I'd appreciate it.

388
00:31:35,640 --> 00:31:37,200
I'll confirm it later in writing.

389
00:31:37,440 --> 00:31:38,160
Thank you.

390
00:31:38,400 --> 00:31:39,640
Good bye, Mr. Molluquet.

391
00:31:54,240 --> 00:31:55,440
We'll order a second one.

392
00:31:55,720 --> 00:31:56,960
It's sad with just one bottle.

393
00:31:57,440 --> 00:31:58,400
It's boring.

394
00:32:01,760 --> 00:32:03,640
I didn't want to lie
to you at the Biarritz.

395
00:32:04,360 --> 00:32:06,200
I just didn't want to oppose you.

396
00:32:07,200 --> 00:32:08,520
You seemed so happy.

397
00:32:11,120 --> 00:32:12,200
And I was in heaven.

398
00:32:13,200 --> 00:32:14,480
I don't really like caviar.

399
00:32:16,680 --> 00:32:18,200
I force myself to eat it.

400
00:32:18,800 --> 00:32:20,120
And with time I'll
start to like it.

401
00:32:21,240 --> 00:32:22,840
I'm sure that when
I start to like it,

402
00:32:24,120 --> 00:32:25,280
it will taste great.

403
00:32:30,560 --> 00:32:31,720
It's nice here, isn't it?

404
00:32:32,400 --> 00:32:34,760
I like this place a lot
because it's not pretentious.

405
00:32:36,080 --> 00:32:37,720
It's calm and grand
at the same time.

406
00:32:39,880 --> 00:32:41,320
We have the impression
that we're unique.

407
00:32:49,600 --> 00:32:50,840
The handle is made from shark bone.

408
00:32:51,120 --> 00:32:52,040
Amazing, isn't it?

409
00:32:52,600 --> 00:32:53,920
The bones are dried for 2 years.

410
00:32:54,560 --> 00:32:56,400
It takes one shark to
make one set of cutlery.

411
00:32:59,920 --> 00:33:00,840
Here you go.

412
00:33:12,120 --> 00:33:13,080
I'm bushed.

413
00:33:14,440 --> 00:33:15,440
I want to go to bed.

414
00:33:16,320 --> 00:33:17,480
At which hotel are you staying?

415
00:33:19,480 --> 00:33:23,040
I found a small, very nice
hotel in the town's suburbs.

416
00:33:23,080 --> 00:33:23,800
Very good.

417
00:33:24,960 --> 00:33:27,200
So go get your stuff
and we'll meet back here.

418
00:33:28,120 --> 00:33:28,720
Here?

419
00:33:29,360 --> 00:33:30,640
It's more simple that way, right?

420
00:33:32,480 --> 00:33:33,080
Yes.

421
00:33:33,400 --> 00:33:34,560
- Is there a problem?
- No.

422
00:33:34,600 --> 00:33:35,480
No. Not at all.

423
00:33:36,360 --> 00:33:37,280
See you later.

424
00:33:58,800 --> 00:33:59,520
Mr. Simon?

425
00:34:00,680 --> 00:34:01,560
Yes, that's right.

426
00:34:02,080 --> 00:34:04,400
Ms. Mercier is waiting
for you in room 304.

427
00:34:04,760 --> 00:34:05,360
Thank you.

428
00:34:05,920 --> 00:34:07,320
Did you enjoy your dinner?

429
00:34:08,320 --> 00:34:09,600
Yes, very much.

430
00:34:09,640 --> 00:34:11,320
May I ask for your credit card?

431
00:34:11,840 --> 00:34:12,600
Excuse me?

432
00:34:13,120 --> 00:34:15,480
Your credit card.
To cover the bill.

433
00:34:15,600 --> 00:34:16,840
Right.
Of course.

434
00:34:29,720 --> 00:34:30,480
Thank you.

435
00:34:32,560 --> 00:34:34,320
Please take Mrs. Pontini's
baggage to her room.

436
00:34:42,560 --> 00:34:44,200
- We're sorry.
- It's alright.

437
00:34:52,720 --> 00:34:53,880
I have exactly the same.

438
00:34:54,240 --> 00:34:55,360
They're the same color?

439
00:34:55,400 --> 00:34:56,160
That's right.

440
00:36:30,280 --> 00:36:30,960
Yes?

441
00:36:32,960 --> 00:36:33,840
Mr. Molluquet.

442
00:36:34,720 --> 00:36:35,480
How are you?

443
00:36:36,880 --> 00:36:37,520
Excuse me?

444
00:36:39,480 --> 00:36:40,240
No.

445
00:36:42,880 --> 00:36:44,280
No one stole my card.

446
00:36:47,160 --> 00:36:48,120
That much?

447
00:36:51,320 --> 00:36:53,920
Please wire the money from my
PEL account to my current account.

448
00:36:55,760 --> 00:36:56,560
And my PEP account?

449
00:36:58,600 --> 00:36:59,440
And my PEA account?

450
00:37:02,120 --> 00:37:03,120
Go ahead.
No problem.

451
00:37:03,800 --> 00:37:04,640
Please do tell me.

452
00:37:04,720 --> 00:37:05,880
Do I have the right to the CEL?

453
00:37:07,000 --> 00:37:07,760
Well that too then.

454
00:37:09,920 --> 00:37:10,960
How much money is in it?

455
00:37:12,960 --> 00:37:13,960
I assumed there's more.

456
00:37:14,680 --> 00:37:15,280
160 EUROS

457
00:37:15,320 --> 00:37:16,200
Well?

458
00:37:17,240 --> 00:37:18,520
Do you really want to go to town?

459
00:37:18,560 --> 00:37:19,200
Yes.

460
00:37:20,080 --> 00:37:20,840
Are you sure?

461
00:37:20,880 --> 00:37:21,960
Yes, why do you ask?

462
00:37:23,360 --> 00:37:23,920
620 EUROS

463
00:37:24,640 --> 00:37:25,440
Why do you ask?

464
00:37:25,960 --> 00:37:26,760
What do you think?

465
00:37:32,440 --> 00:37:33,440
300 EUROS

466
00:37:35,000 --> 00:37:35,920
What's wrong?

467
00:37:36,520 --> 00:37:37,400
Nothing.

468
00:37:37,360 --> 00:37:38,000
Good.

469
00:37:41,800 --> 00:37:42,400
Can we go?

470
00:37:46,400 --> 00:37:47,640
You can't continue doing this.

471
00:37:47,880 --> 00:37:49,680
This is my business.
I'm paying, right?

472
00:37:51,920 --> 00:37:52,520
Indeed.

473
00:37:54,600 --> 00:37:55,680
And that's what counts, right?

474
00:37:58,880 --> 00:37:59,600
Indeed.

475
00:37:59,640 --> 00:38:00,440
So what's wrong?

476
00:38:00,480 --> 00:38:01,240
Nothing.

477
00:38:01,280 --> 00:38:02,120
So let's go for a walk.

478
00:38:02,160 --> 00:38:03,240
I don't want to go for a walk.

479
00:38:04,080 --> 00:38:05,080
What do you want?

480
00:38:14,840 --> 00:38:15,920
I want a handbag.

481
00:38:25,800 --> 00:38:26,520
What is it?

482
00:38:28,360 --> 00:38:30,480
I feel good, because I'm
not working this afternoon.

483
00:38:31,240 --> 00:38:32,640
I feel like I'm skipping class.

484
00:38:34,880 --> 00:38:35,600
Me too.

485
00:38:37,800 --> 00:38:38,920
On top of that I'm drunk.

486
00:38:40,400 --> 00:38:42,480
Better to be drunk in the
afternoon than in the evening.

487
00:38:42,840 --> 00:38:43,920
It's much better this way.

488
00:38:46,920 --> 00:38:48,600
We have the impression
we're keeping a secret.

489
00:38:50,960 --> 00:38:52,880
Would you like anything else?
Maybe some ice cream?

490
00:38:53,480 --> 00:38:54,320
I want a dress.

491
00:39:15,840 --> 00:39:16,360
Have mercy.

492
00:39:16,400 --> 00:39:17,600
OPERATION CAN'T BE PERFORMED

493
00:39:22,600 --> 00:39:24,320
THANK YOU FOR YOUR VISIT

494
00:39:29,240 --> 00:39:30,880
This one is gorgeous.

495
00:39:46,800 --> 00:39:48,400
Castelles cake!
I love it!

496
00:40:20,880 --> 00:40:21,760
Here you go.

497
00:40:22,440 --> 00:40:23,880
I got you a place in first class.

498
00:40:26,040 --> 00:40:26,760
Thank you.

499
00:40:29,080 --> 00:40:30,080
So, good bye.

500
00:40:30,840 --> 00:40:31,480
Good bye.

501
00:40:33,000 --> 00:40:33,680
Wait.

502
00:40:39,680 --> 00:40:40,520
Another 10 seconds.

503
00:41:02,800 --> 00:41:03,600
The 10 seconds are up.

504
00:41:14,440 --> 00:41:15,160
Fine.

505
00:41:16,640 --> 00:41:17,280
Fine.

506
00:41:18,600 --> 00:41:19,520
Fine, thank you.

507
00:41:21,880 --> 00:41:23,120
Ask Jeff to come here.

508
00:41:24,040 --> 00:41:25,320
You're not looking for a barman?

509
00:41:25,360 --> 00:41:26,400
I have very good credentials.

510
00:41:26,800 --> 00:41:27,560
No, sir.

511
00:41:29,000 --> 00:41:31,480
I'm sorry sir, but I'm
forced to call the police.

512
00:41:31,880 --> 00:41:33,240
Can't we work something out?

513
00:41:34,280 --> 00:41:37,680
Pool man, room service,
porter, driver?

514
00:41:37,800 --> 00:41:38,440
No, sir.

515
00:41:38,800 --> 00:41:39,720
- Excuse me.
- Yes?

516
00:41:40,160 --> 00:41:41,880
Can someone give me
a hand with my bag?

517
00:41:41,920 --> 00:41:43,400
I'll send over Benoit.

518
00:41:43,440 --> 00:41:45,160
Don't trouble yourself.

519
00:41:46,760 --> 00:41:49,000
My friend will be delighted
to give me a hand.

520
00:41:54,280 --> 00:41:56,640
You were very eager to
help me last time.

521
00:42:32,800 --> 00:42:37,120
Add the bill of room 304
to the account of room 429.

522
00:42:47,320 --> 00:42:49,960
- Shall we get out?
- Yes, of course.

523
00:43:06,200 --> 00:43:07,080
And?

524
00:43:10,600 --> 00:43:11,800
Will you close the door?

525
00:43:12,040 --> 00:43:12,680
Yes.

526
00:44:05,320 --> 00:44:06,000
Good evening.

527
00:44:14,400 --> 00:44:15,480
Which floor?

528
00:44:15,920 --> 00:44:16,760
The third floor.

529
00:45:13,200 --> 00:45:14,200
Good morning, sir.

530
00:45:14,720 --> 00:45:15,360
Good morning.

531
00:45:27,520 --> 00:45:28,320
Is everything alright?

532
00:45:31,680 --> 00:45:33,680
Impossible.
You'll never go away.

533
00:45:33,720 --> 00:45:34,600
This isn't about you.

534
00:45:34,640 --> 00:45:36,040
Yesterday I had a
problem with paying...

535
00:45:36,080 --> 00:45:37,720
You have to leave me alone,
do you understand?

536
00:45:38,000 --> 00:45:38,920
I have to work, Jean.

537
00:45:39,200 --> 00:45:39,880
Calm down.

538
00:45:39,920 --> 00:45:41,720
Do you think you can
go around having a crush?

539
00:45:41,840 --> 00:45:42,560
It's not about that.

540
00:45:42,600 --> 00:45:44,960
I met this woman and
she made me an offer...

541
00:45:45,000 --> 00:45:45,840
Stop it.

542
00:45:45,880 --> 00:45:46,880
I know why you're here.

543
00:45:47,080 --> 00:45:48,120
I'm telling the truth.

544
00:45:48,160 --> 00:45:49,560
You think I don't know
what's going on?

545
00:45:49,680 --> 00:45:50,720
That I don't know that look?

546
00:45:51,800 --> 00:45:53,600
Since I was 12 I've seen that look.

547
00:46:03,120 --> 00:46:04,080
Good morning, Madeleine.

548
00:46:04,400 --> 00:46:05,160
Did you sleep well?

549
00:46:05,520 --> 00:46:06,560
Very well, thank you.

550
00:46:07,400 --> 00:46:08,360
Have you picked something?

551
00:46:08,520 --> 00:46:09,160
Excuse me?

552
00:46:09,680 --> 00:46:10,600
Have you been served?

553
00:46:10,800 --> 00:46:12,440
No, but everything is fine.

554
00:46:12,840 --> 00:46:14,040
Won't you sit down?

555
00:46:16,400 --> 00:46:17,360
Excuse me.

556
00:46:32,040 --> 00:46:33,320
Shall I bring you something?

557
00:46:33,840 --> 00:46:35,800
Not now.
That's nice of you, thank you.

558
00:47:27,400 --> 00:47:28,080
What's going on?

559
00:47:29,840 --> 00:47:30,960
You had a bad dream.

560
00:47:31,440 --> 00:47:32,880
But that's good because
now you're awake.

561
00:47:32,920 --> 00:47:34,040
