837
01:04:51,680 --> 01:04:52,600
I went to the bathroom.

838
01:04:53,200 --> 01:04:55,360
Two visits to the bathroom
during a meal at your age?

839
01:04:56,320 --> 01:04:57,600
I'm sorry... I...

840
01:04:59,400 --> 01:05:00,320
What were you doing?

841
01:05:00,640 --> 01:05:01,760
Were you talking to someone?

842
01:05:02,120 --> 01:05:03,160
No.

843
01:05:03,480 --> 01:05:04,520
You can tell me.

844
01:05:04,960 --> 01:05:05,840
No.

845
01:05:06,520 --> 01:05:08,640
You weren't talking to anyone
or you don't want to tell me?

846
01:05:09,120 --> 01:05:11,440
I'm not jealous just curious.

847
01:05:17,480 --> 01:05:18,560
I...

848
01:05:21,720 --> 01:05:23,200
What's wrong, Jean?

849
01:05:23,320 --> 01:05:24,640
Nothing... I...

850
01:05:26,560 --> 01:05:27,720
I want to...

851
01:05:29,560 --> 01:05:30,920
I'd like to...

852
01:05:32,560 --> 01:05:33,840
Enough of this.

853
01:05:34,960 --> 01:05:36,080
What do you think you're doing?

854
01:05:37,160 --> 01:05:38,800
That you can play games with me

855
01:05:38,840 --> 01:05:40,200
like with a young virgin?

856
01:05:42,480 --> 01:05:43,840
Listen to me carefully, my boy.

857
01:05:44,440 --> 01:05:46,200
If I want to I can
throw you out of here

858
01:05:46,240 --> 01:05:47,760
with one snap of my fingers.

859
01:05:48,960 --> 01:05:51,960
So if you want to continue
to enjoy the pool and the boutiques,

860
01:05:53,080 --> 01:05:55,240
then you better show
some more concentration.

861
01:05:57,080 --> 01:05:58,200
Do you understand?

862
01:07:01,280 --> 01:07:02,520
I'm sorry I'm late.

863
01:07:03,880 --> 01:07:05,200
We visited the boutiques.

864
01:07:13,120 --> 01:07:14,920
- She bought you a scooter?
- Yes.

865
01:07:15,240 --> 01:07:16,400
It has a luggage box.

866
01:07:17,000 --> 01:07:18,040
And a full tank.

867
01:07:19,600 --> 01:07:20,760
We can go for a swim.

868
01:07:21,640 --> 01:07:22,880
I know this nice place by the sea.

869
01:07:22,920 --> 01:07:24,680
I've been wanting to go
there since arriving here.

870
01:07:24,840 --> 01:07:25,840
We'll go there now.

871
01:07:27,440 --> 01:07:28,880
Order me a glass and
I'll be right back.

872
01:07:44,240 --> 01:07:45,840
We made a good choice
by picking this suit.

873
01:07:45,880 --> 01:07:46,680
It's very nice.

874
01:08:07,800 --> 01:08:09,080
- Good night.
- Good night.

875
01:08:24,120 --> 01:08:25,200
You were right.

876
01:08:25,200 --> 01:08:27,760
It's good to go to bed early.

877
01:08:36,000 --> 01:08:38,880
It was nice of you to cancel
our dinner at the restaurant.

878
01:08:39,040 --> 01:08:39,840
Really?

879
01:08:40,040 --> 01:08:43,120
Yes. It's as if you gave me a gift.

880
01:08:45,080 --> 01:08:47,200
- Thank you.
- Don't mention it.

881
01:08:54,000 --> 01:08:55,640
You're really not hungry this evening?

882
01:08:56,840 --> 01:08:57,680
No I'm not.

883
01:08:58,080 --> 01:08:59,240
That's something rare, isn't it?

884
01:09:00,160 --> 01:09:00,920
That's true.

885
01:09:09,520 --> 01:09:10,840
Do you want some candy?

886
01:09:11,880 --> 01:09:12,880
No, thank you.

887
01:09:13,880 --> 01:09:16,320
I own some of the producer's stock.
It makes me good money.

888
01:09:29,440 --> 01:09:30,600
Where are you from?

889
01:09:32,200 --> 01:09:33,200
Excuse me?

890
01:09:33,360 --> 01:09:34,640
Where are you from?

891
01:09:34,800 --> 01:09:35,720
I'm from Saint-Brieux.

892
01:09:35,760 --> 01:09:36,840
Saint-Brieux?

893
01:09:42,080 --> 01:09:43,120
Is it nice there?

894
01:09:45,120 --> 01:09:46,040
It rains all the time.

895
01:09:50,280 --> 01:09:53,080
Do you know that I haven't
seen the rain in 4 years?

896
01:09:54,880 --> 01:09:56,000
It's always summer here.

897
01:09:59,200 --> 01:10:01,120
I miss the smell of rain.

898
01:10:13,760 --> 01:10:15,040
Do you have any siblings?

899
01:10:19,720 --> 01:10:20,480
No.

900
01:10:23,360 --> 01:10:25,600
I have 2 brothers and 3 sisters.

901
01:10:25,800 --> 01:10:27,320
And my oldest sister
would always tease me.

902
01:10:27,800 --> 01:10:28,840
I mean that...

903
01:11:40,440 --> 01:11:41,440
You haven't said anything.

904
01:11:42,000 --> 01:11:43,600
It's very nice here.

905
01:11:44,960 --> 01:11:46,120
I lack the words to describe it.

906
01:11:49,640 --> 01:11:51,440
Behind us is an abandoned vineyard.

907
01:11:52,160 --> 01:11:54,120
I find grapes there in September.

908
01:11:55,760 --> 01:11:57,160
And up there, to your left...

909
01:11:58,040 --> 01:11:59,280
There's an old sheep house.

910
01:11:59,400 --> 01:12:00,240
Do you see it?

911
01:12:00,440 --> 01:12:02,080
I can barely see my sandwich.

912
01:12:30,920 --> 01:12:32,240
Dammit.
Impossible.

913
01:13:54,840 --> 01:13:55,760
Jean, excuse me.

914
01:13:55,800 --> 01:13:58,640
It would be lovely if you could
bring me my book from our room.

915
01:14:11,480 --> 01:14:12,440
Irene?

916
01:14:13,560 --> 01:14:14,480
Is everything alright?

917
01:14:16,120 --> 01:14:18,320
I wanted to tell you that
I spent a wonderful night.

918
01:14:19,720 --> 01:14:20,680
Me too.

919
01:14:21,920 --> 01:14:23,040
When can we do it again?

920
01:14:25,600 --> 01:14:27,200
I didn't want to
fall asleep, you know.

921
01:14:29,160 --> 01:14:30,680
So that I could savor each minute.

922
01:14:32,880 --> 01:14:33,960
What's wrong?

923
01:14:40,520 --> 01:14:41,360
I'm leaving.

924
01:14:43,800 --> 01:14:44,880
I came to say good bye.

925
01:14:47,720 --> 01:14:48,600
Where to?

926
01:14:50,280 --> 01:14:51,360
I'm going to Venice.

927
01:14:52,520 --> 01:14:53,440
With Gilles.

928
01:14:54,160 --> 01:14:55,400
And then to the Maldives.

929
01:14:58,880 --> 01:14:59,720
When?

930
01:15:01,880 --> 01:15:02,840
This evening.

931
01:15:07,440 --> 01:15:08,400
When are you coming back?

932
01:15:10,280 --> 01:15:11,160
I'm not coming back.

933
01:15:15,320 --> 01:15:17,800
When I was a kid I went to
Venice once with my parents.

934
01:15:19,600 --> 01:15:23,080
I remember the bread rolls
they had there. I adored them.

935
01:15:25,600 --> 01:15:26,920
I don't remember their name.

936
01:15:29,960 --> 01:15:30,960
Do you know which ones?

937
01:15:30,960 --> 01:15:32,080
Yes.

938
01:15:33,000 --> 01:15:34,640
I also don't remember their name.

939
01:15:36,720 --> 01:15:38,000
And I also adore them.

940
01:15:45,200 --> 01:15:46,600
So... good bye.

941
01:16:21,880 --> 01:16:23,120
Jean, are you here?

942
01:16:50,720 --> 01:16:51,520
Here you are.

943
01:16:52,480 --> 01:16:53,280
Is everything alright?

944
01:16:53,640 --> 01:16:54,320
Yes.

945
01:16:55,280 --> 01:16:56,160
The book was here.

946
01:16:56,600 --> 01:16:57,480
Thank you.

947
01:16:59,880 --> 01:17:03,840
Madeleine, what's the name of
those Italian bread rolls?

948
01:17:14,440 --> 01:17:15,200
Oh no...

949
01:17:15,400 --> 01:17:16,480
Oh no, this can't be true...

950
01:17:16,520 --> 01:17:18,080
That bastard...
Not again...

951
01:17:24,680 --> 01:17:25,800
Dammit...

952
01:17:51,320 --> 01:17:52,680
The bread rolls are called panettones.

953
01:17:53,240 --> 01:17:54,400
That idiot dumped me.

954
01:17:55,040 --> 01:17:55,960
He dumped you?

955
01:17:57,000 --> 01:17:57,920
He left me here.

956
01:17:58,360 --> 01:17:59,280
And took everything.

957
01:17:59,320 --> 01:18:00,000
But why?

958
01:18:00,440 --> 01:18:01,320
And what do you think?

959
01:18:01,880 --> 01:18:02,800
Do you think he saw us?

960
01:18:02,840 --> 01:18:04,000
Of course he saw us.

961
01:18:04,880 --> 01:18:07,040
I can't believe it.
I'm so stupid.

962
01:18:08,440 --> 01:18:09,760
You have to go to the train station.

963
01:18:10,960 --> 01:18:12,760
I keep my things there
in a luggage box.

964
01:18:13,400 --> 01:18:14,480
Dammit... I have nothing.

965
01:18:15,200 --> 01:18:18,480
I only have this cover
and the swimming suit.

966
01:19:39,920 --> 01:19:40,920
Miss?

967
01:19:41,720 --> 01:19:42,640
This is for you.

968
01:19:53,280 --> 01:19:54,880
The room has been paid
for the whole week.

969
01:19:58,200 --> 01:19:59,320
Are you alright?

970
01:19:59,360 --> 01:20:00,200
Yes.
I'm fine.

971
01:20:02,000 --> 01:20:03,240
You look a little nervous.

972
01:20:03,280 --> 01:20:04,240
No, I'm not nervous.

973
01:20:06,800 --> 01:20:07,720
What will you have?

974
01:20:08,240 --> 01:20:09,160
I'll have a vodka.

975
01:20:09,200 --> 01:20:11,480
We'll have a scotch
whisky and a vodka.

976
01:20:12,720 --> 01:20:13,800
Where's your watch?

977
01:20:16,000 --> 01:20:16,800
I sold it.

978
01:20:19,200 --> 01:20:20,560
That's not true.
It's in our room.

979
01:20:21,120 --> 01:20:22,760
No, I sold it at the same boutique.

980
01:20:24,800 --> 01:20:25,480
But...

981
01:20:25,520 --> 01:20:26,640
It was mine, wasn't it?

982
01:20:28,720 --> 01:20:29,520
Yes.

983
01:20:37,080 --> 01:20:39,040
I wanted to believe
you're a little different.

984
01:20:39,400 --> 01:20:40,640
Not like the others.

985
01:20:41,520 --> 01:20:43,320
But you're only more
clever than they are.

986
01:20:44,000 --> 01:20:45,200
I don't know what came over me.

987
01:20:46,600 --> 01:20:48,440
I wanted to buy you a gift,
but I had no money.

988
01:20:50,800 --> 01:20:52,920
So... here you go.

989
01:20:58,240 --> 01:20:59,480
They're gorgeous.

990
01:21:05,840 --> 01:21:07,240
This is charming, Jean.

991
01:21:08,840 --> 01:21:10,800
That watch was the
only thing you had.

992
01:21:30,640 --> 01:21:32,480
I'm sure I gave you the invitation.

993
01:21:33,240 --> 01:21:36,000
No. The invitation was
on your nightstand.

994
01:21:37,880 --> 01:21:39,240
Most likely the cleaning
lady took it.

995
01:21:39,640 --> 01:21:40,640
It doesn't matter.

996
01:22:28,720 --> 01:22:29,800
Excuse me.

997
01:22:30,440 --> 01:22:31,680
Do you have a light?

998
01:23:11,040 --> 01:23:12,720
Can I bring you some champagne?

999
01:23:12,760 --> 01:23:13,920
That would be charming.

1000
01:23:39,280 --> 01:23:40,480
5 glasses, please.

1001
01:24:23,480 --> 01:24:24,400
Thank you.

1002
01:24:49,120 --> 01:24:50,200
You're a prince.

1003
01:25:11,280 --> 01:25:12,840
I will be needing your help, Jean.

1004
01:25:12,920 --> 01:25:14,160
Of course. How can I help?

1005
01:25:16,040 --> 01:25:17,200
I saw Jacques.

1006
01:25:19,640 --> 01:25:20,640
You need to help me.

1007
01:25:20,760 --> 01:25:21,600
In what way?

1008
01:25:22,880 --> 01:25:23,920
I want you to help me...

1009
01:25:25,680 --> 01:25:26,640
seduce him.

1010
01:25:31,080 --> 01:25:32,680
Things can't go on like this, Jean.

1011
01:25:33,880 --> 01:25:35,480
That situation at the
pool was just too hard.

1012
01:25:35,520 --> 01:25:37,440
I don't want to find myself
without anything again.

1013
01:25:38,720 --> 01:25:39,520
I prefer to...

1014
01:25:39,560 --> 01:25:40,720
What do you want me to do?

1015
01:25:43,280 --> 01:25:44,280
Tell me.

1016
01:26:01,200 --> 01:26:02,000
Excuse me.

1017
01:26:02,040 --> 01:26:03,440
A glass of champagne, please.

1018
01:26:05,560 --> 01:26:06,840
One for you?

1019
01:26:07,240 --> 01:26:07,920
Yes.

1020
01:26:08,040 --> 01:26:09,480
One more glass, please.

1021
01:26:10,320 --> 01:26:11,040
Thank you.

1022
01:26:12,320 --> 01:26:13,840
Getting some champagne is real madness.

1023
01:26:14,080 --> 01:26:14,960
When did you arrive?

1024
01:26:15,240 --> 01:26:16,520
About 10 minutes ago.

1025
01:26:16,840 --> 01:26:17,600
Are you alone?

1026
01:26:18,160 --> 01:26:19,360
Yes, for now.

1027
01:26:19,800 --> 01:26:21,480
- And you?
- No.

1028
01:26:23,920 --> 01:26:25,240
Here's to our health.

1029
01:26:26,040 --> 01:26:27,280
- Irene.
- Agnes.

1030
01:26:31,880 --> 01:26:33,000
Impossible...

1031
01:26:33,280 --> 01:26:33,920
What?

1032
01:26:34,800 --> 01:26:36,200
This is my lucky day.

1033
01:26:36,480 --> 01:26:37,280
What is it?

1034
01:26:37,840 --> 01:26:39,560
- The Prince von Hoffenberg.
- Who?

1035
01:26:39,920 --> 01:26:42,280
The Prince von Hoffenberg.
There, near the roses.

1036
01:26:42,840 --> 01:26:43,760
Who is he?

1037
01:26:44,320 --> 01:26:45,600
A mover and shaker of this world.

1038
01:26:47,160 --> 01:26:48,520
He's a Dutch nobleman.

1039
01:26:48,760 --> 01:26:50,800
And he's an industrial tycoon.

1040
01:26:52,320 --> 01:26:53,520
He must have just arrived.

1041
01:26:55,000 --> 01:26:56,000
He's very rich

1042
01:26:56,680 --> 01:26:57,640
and very lonely.

1043
01:26:58,680 --> 01:27:01,000
He lost his wife in
a car accident 2 years ago.

1044
01:27:01,640 --> 01:27:03,400
And since then he's
in such a poor shape.

1045
01:27:06,080 --> 01:27:07,520
I'll go to him
and take my chances.

1046
01:27:07,880 --> 01:27:09,040
Excuse me.

1047
01:27:16,880 --> 01:27:17,880
Is it at her you're looking?

1048
01:27:19,400 --> 01:27:20,200
Yes.

1049
01:27:20,920 --> 01:27:21,960
Is she looking at you?

1050
01:27:22,000 --> 01:27:24,880
Yes. She's taking shy
glances at me.

1051
01:27:25,400 --> 01:27:26,560
She wants to get married.

1052
01:27:27,360 --> 01:27:28,240
Here you go.

1053
01:27:28,560 --> 01:27:29,880
I noticed you hadn't any left.

1054
01:27:31,040 --> 01:27:31,880
Thank you.

1055
01:27:32,080 --> 01:27:33,040
Good evening.

1056
01:27:34,240 --> 01:27:35,560
This is Agnes, my friend.

1057
01:27:36,640 --> 01:27:38,600
- Prince Michel...
- ...von Hoffenberg.

1058
01:27:38,800 --> 01:27:39,520
Of course.

1059
01:27:40,400 --> 01:27:41,760
- Good evening.
- Good evening.

1060
01:27:42,360 --> 01:27:43,480
I'm rarely recognized.

1061
01:27:43,840 --> 01:27:46,040
But you have a face
that's impossible to forget.

1062
01:27:47,920 --> 01:27:48,920
Have you just arrived?

1063
01:27:48,800 --> 01:27:50,280
I don't intend to
stay here too long.

1064
01:27:50,320 --> 01:27:52,440
- I think this is a little...
- Yes, that's true.

1065
01:27:52,480 --> 01:27:53,240
You think the same?

1066
01:27:57,600 --> 01:28:00,200
I couldn't help myself from
looking at you all evening.

1067
01:28:00,240 --> 01:28:00,880
I'm sorry.

1068
01:28:01,720 --> 01:28:02,720
No need to be sorry.

1069
01:28:04,000 --> 01:28:05,360
You remind me of someone.

1070
01:28:06,240 --> 01:28:07,400
The Princess of Edinburgh.

1071
01:28:09,280 --> 01:28:10,840
- Excuse me, Ines.
- Irene.

1072
01:28:11,440 --> 01:28:12,360
I'm sorry.

1073
01:28:12,400 --> 01:28:14,520
Don't mention it.
Maybe we can see each other later?

1074
01:28:16,720 --> 01:28:19,520
I have her portrait, painted by
Rembrandt, at my country house.

1075
01:28:21,400 --> 01:28:22,560
I hung it in the guest room.

1076
01:28:24,360 --> 01:28:25,600
I'd like to show it to you.

1077
01:28:26,120 --> 01:28:27,200
The resemblance is striking.

1078
01:28:28,760 --> 01:28:30,840
She was executed during the revolution.

1079
01:28:30,880 --> 01:28:32,760
Oh my God...
I'm so sorry.

1080
01:28:33,320 --> 01:28:34,400
The pain has passed.

1081
01:28:38,400 --> 01:28:39,920
Excuse me for a moment.

1082
01:28:43,720 --> 01:28:45,880
You're behaving like a rude bastard.

1083
01:28:46,040 --> 01:28:48,320
For the past hour you've been
going from one woman to the next.

1084
01:28:49,000 --> 01:28:50,600
What are you doing?
Who do you think you are?

1085
01:28:51,240 --> 01:28:52,600
Do you think a little
jewel is enough?

1086
01:28:52,640 --> 01:28:53,520
I'm sorry, Madeleine.

1087
01:28:53,600 --> 01:28:55,040
I don't give a damn
that you're sorry.

1088
01:28:55,080 --> 01:28:57,520
You told my friends you'll
bring us some champagne, so do it.

1089
01:28:57,560 --> 01:28:58,800
You have 2 minutes to bring it.

1090
01:28:58,840 --> 01:29:00,760
I'd be happy to help, but I can't.

1091
01:29:01,440 --> 01:29:02,440
What do you mean you can't?

1092
01:29:04,000 --> 01:29:06,560
I need to go to the hotel and
spend a few hours with this girl.

1093
01:29:08,440 --> 01:29:09,440
What are you talking about?

1094
01:29:09,680 --> 01:29:11,240
I need to do a favor.
I can't do otherwise.

1095
01:29:11,720 --> 01:29:12,720
Are you kidding me?

1096
01:29:12,760 --> 01:29:13,360
I'm warning you.

1097
01:29:13,400 --> 01:29:15,960
If you leave with that girl,
don't count on me, understand?

1098
01:29:16,840 --> 01:29:19,400
I'll leave the scooter at the
parking lot and the keys at reception.

1099
01:29:25,400 --> 01:29:27,000
There's nothing I can
do to stop you?

1100
01:29:27,040 --> 01:29:27,840
No.

1101
01:29:30,720 --> 01:29:31,400
I'm sorry.

1102
01:29:31,440 --> 01:29:33,320
Stop being so nice.
It's unbearable.

1103
01:29:35,600 --> 01:29:37,720
It seems that a man
like you can't be bought.

1104
01:29:37,880 --> 01:29:38,800
Even by me.

1105
01:29:41,920 --> 01:29:43,920
I'll be fine, don't worry.
You're not the first.

1106
01:29:43,960 --> 01:29:45,480
Thank you for approaching
things this way.

1107
01:29:46,640 --> 01:29:47,960
Do I have a choice?

1108
01:29:53,800 --> 01:29:55,160
You can keep the scooter.

1109
01:29:55,600 --> 01:29:56,680
You deserve it.

1110
01:30:06,520 --> 01:30:07,440
I'm sorry...

1111
01:30:08,360 --> 01:30:09,520
That was my ex mother-in-law.

1112
01:30:10,000 --> 01:30:11,400
The Baroness von Bosten.

1113
01:30:11,440 --> 01:30:13,560
She can't stand that
I talk to other women since...

1114
01:30:13,600 --> 01:30:14,280
Yes.

1115
01:30:14,440 --> 01:30:15,240
I know.

1116
01:30:19,160 --> 01:30:20,360
Don't hold it against her.

1117
01:30:20,400 --> 01:30:21,520
She's suffering because of it.

1118
01:30:22,000 --> 01:30:23,440
But I have to live on, right?

1119
01:30:23,680 --> 01:30:25,920
Yes, of course.
One must live on.

1120
01:30:26,480 --> 01:30:27,600
Life goes on.

1121
01:30:32,200 --> 01:30:33,040
Are you alright?

1122
01:30:33,200 --> 01:30:35,320
No...
Yes.

1123
01:30:36,800 --> 01:30:37,680
I want to...

1124
01:30:38,440 --> 01:30:39,400
I'd like to...

1125
01:31:20,280 --> 01:31:21,360
Well well.

1126
01:31:21,840 --> 01:31:22,800
Good evening, Jacques.

1127
01:31:23,000 --> 01:31:24,240
Good evening, Irene.

1128
01:31:24,400 --> 01:31:26,760
You see. I still
remember your name.

1129
01:31:28,040 --> 01:31:28,800
Are you alone?

1130
01:31:29,240 --> 01:31:30,040
As you can see.

1131
01:31:45,000 --> 01:31:46,920
What have you been doing?

1132
01:31:47,200 --> 01:31:48,320
I've been signing checks.

1133
01:31:49,480 --> 01:31:50,320
When did you arrive?

1134
01:31:52,040 --> 01:31:54,720
I arrived this morning.
I was dumped this evening.

1135
01:31:55,880 --> 01:31:57,120
Not all is lost.

1136
01:31:58,720 --> 01:31:59,480
It seems so.

1137
01:32:04,800 --> 01:32:07,680
I think I've already
forgotten her name.

1138
01:32:09,840 --> 01:32:11,000
Excuse me.
What did you say?

1139
01:32:11,520 --> 01:32:13,680
That I've already
forgotten her name.

1140
01:32:16,080 --> 01:32:17,000
Agnes.

1141
01:32:17,600 --> 01:32:18,520
You know her?

1142
01:32:20,680 --> 01:32:21,760
Small world.

1143
01:32:23,480 --> 01:32:24,760
Are you alright?

1144
01:32:26,800 --> 01:32:28,800
Yes. I'm fine.

1145
01:32:29,720 --> 01:32:31,960
Do you have any plans
for the coming days?

1146
01:32:34,320 --> 01:32:35,480
Do you have any plans?

1147
01:32:36,760 --> 01:32:37,520
Excuse me?

1148
01:32:38,800 --> 01:32:41,800
I have this impression
your thoughts are elsewhere.

1149
01:32:42,440 --> 01:32:43,960
And I don't like it.

1150
01:32:45,760 --> 01:32:46,640
Excuse me.

1151
01:32:46,960 --> 01:32:47,720
Pardon me.

1152
01:32:47,920 --> 01:32:49,840
It's the alcohol and the fatigue.

1153
01:32:51,200 --> 01:32:52,320
I'm falling asleep.

1154
01:32:53,480 --> 01:32:54,400
What were you saying?

1155
01:32:55,160 --> 01:32:56,840
I asked if you had any plans.

1156
01:32:59,760 --> 01:33:01,600
What are you plans
for the coming days?

1157
01:33:07,840 --> 01:33:08,760
Love.

1158
01:33:12,760 --> 01:33:14,000
I plan to make love.

1159
01:33:15,880 --> 01:33:16,840
Excuse me.

1160
01:33:17,640 --> 01:33:18,520
Excuse me, Jacques.

1161
01:33:18,920 --> 01:33:19,720
I'm sorry.

1162
01:33:21,280 --> 01:33:22,040
Excuse me.

1163
01:33:23,440 --> 01:33:24,680
I'm really sorry.

1164
01:34:20,000 --> 01:34:21,840
Prince?
What's going on?

1165
01:34:24,160 --> 01:34:25,360
What are you doing here?

1166
01:34:25,400 --> 01:34:26,360
I'm doing you a favor.

1167
01:34:27,200 --> 01:34:28,240
He's not a prince.

1168
01:34:37,200 --> 01:34:38,160
I can't believe it.

1169
01:34:39,320 --> 01:34:40,040
Excuse me.

1170
01:34:42,000 --> 01:34:42,880
Well...

1171
01:34:43,600 --> 01:34:44,640
It took you a while.

1172
01:34:45,960 --> 01:34:47,080
I did what I could.

1173
01:34:57,680 --> 01:34:58,840
I want to...

1174
01:35:01,000 --> 01:35:02,040
I'd like to...

1175
01:35:07,680 --> 01:35:08,960
Kiss you.

1176
